place_description: Seattle-based coffeehouse chain known for its signature roasts, light bites and WiFi availability.

reviews_data.review_text: I frequent this location and usually have a good experience. I order through the app and usually just select previous order each time. I came to get my drink and it was a grande matcha. I told them it should've been a venti. A lady that worked there was like well you ordered a grande in the app. I said it must be a mistake and said I would pay the difference for a venti. She reprimanded me in front of everyone and just said next time update it on the app. I looked in the app and it was my mistake which I even admitted to in the store. I didn't appreciate being talked down to when I was willing to pay the difference and even admitted that maybe I made a mistake.
I drank something hard that wouldn't break even when pressed hard. I suspect it's rubber.

I had to write a review because the service I received at the University location was exceptional and Park Road was so poor in customer service. I was there about a week ago and I had to go back in because my drink was wrong, the man who made my drink passively aggressively FORCED me to tell how I wanted my drink and how he should make it. It was so uncomfortable.

At university they were kind and when my drink was wrong they remade it with a smile and we laughed about it. The Barista didn't roll her eyes and force me to tell her how I want my drink made when I don't know the ingredients Starbucks does. There are reviews that are countless with poor service. Please do not come hwre

I recently visited the Starbucks on Park Road around 10:30 a.m on Sunday 10/27/2024 and picked up my usual drink. When I tasted it, something seemed off, so I went back to ask if it could be remade. I politely spoke with a barista (who I later found out was also the manager). She agreed to remake the drink but did so with visible frustration. She grabbed my drink and threw it away forcefully, causing some coffee to splash onto my sweater.

Her attitude was rude and unprofessional, and I felt disrespected, especially as an Asian customer. It seemed as though she assumed I didn't understand English well, making the interaction uncomfortable and upsetting. I've been coming here every Sunday, and everyone else has always been respectful and welcoming. This was the first time I experienced such rude treatment, and I hope Starbucks ensures this behavior never happens again. I will be contacting Starbucks corporate to report this incident, and the District Manager can check the camera footage at that time to confirm what happened.

It's helpful to understand that the SBucks plaza is deceiving HUGE. Two levels of shops & restaurants cover 1/2 a city block. Yeah. The plaza traffic gets crazy CONGESTED. Oddly parked delivery trucks and illegal, fire-lane-parked customers add to the mayhem. You'll be shocked and annoyed unless you know this in advance.

So chill out, drive past SBucks' 5 little parking spaces and into the big main lot where there's always space, even if it's all the way in the back by the treeline. Once legally parked, it's a short stoll to SBucks (and some unique shops).
